An Energy Audit is done by comparingindoor
temperature of a building to theoutdoor
temperature of a building
The data plotted consists of more than 14 000
temperaturemeasurements collected during
February - March. A lot of the meassurements
where takenwhen the outside temperatrue
where around 0°C or -12°C.To get a better view
we need to normalize the data.
Normalized data shows theaverage and the
distrobutionof readings instead of the actual
meter points.There needs to beenough points
collected at eachoutdoor temperatre interval
lin order for us to see howthe systems works at
that temperature.In this example there is no
data fortemperatures above 7°C
In well adjusted heatng system the indoor
temperaturewill be the same regardless of out
door temperature.However some variation will
always occur.Typically there is a big variation
in the range 0-4°C since otherparameters such
as humidity and wind varies a lotin this inter
vall.
In well adjusted heatng system the tempera
turefrom different appertments or different
roomsin an appartment will also be the same.
